What you need to know:

Norris Ongalo, the Chief Safety Manager for the famous round of the WRC series, will deploy about 2,487 personnel from various sections of the safety and security departments of the Safari RallySpeaking on Zoom link from Geneva, Dussausaye said group of about 70 persons, that will include foreign and local photographers and journalists, will be allowed as registered mediaThe rally will take place in the Great Rift Valley, around Lake Naivasha and Elmenteita with the Service Park being at the KWS Training Institute in Naivasha